<p>GigaCheck employs a dual-metric evaluation strategy tailored to each tas=
k:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Classification</strong>: Uses <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5=
e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:h=
idden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">eval/mean_cls_accuracy</code> to m=
easure document-level prediction correctness, evaluated every 81 training s=
teps</li>
<li><strong>Detection</strong>: Uses <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5]=
 px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden=
 after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">eval_mAP@0.5-0.95</code> to measure int=
erval localization quality across multiple IoU thresholds, evaluated every =
epoch</li>
</ul>
<p>Both metrics integrate seamlessly with the HuggingFace Trainer ecosystem=
, enabling automated checkpoint selection, TensorBoard logging, and early s=
topping strategies. The metrics align with established evaluation protocols=
 in their respective domains (classification accuracy and COCO-style mAP fo=
r object detection).</p>
